spanGrp.span: nam baptaes sok ih nge Ibraem
mi baptaes nem blong mi Ibraem
nam longbini ka nap pune punen ne kastom
I want to tell a story of our tradition
mi wantem talem stori blong kastom
ke yaapuo ngyee lam mela lan mange van lam mee mal
that men went up the mange hierarchy, they became chief.
we ol man oli jamp long mange oli kam oli kam hae man
anap pun ne gon van akap kiibele
I will tell so that you know
bae mi talem nomo blong yufala i save
bi(li) ke vanten mwe stat ka be van bo top popat ka be mee be mee e yaapuo
that a man started to kill a pig in order to become a high man.
taem man i stat blong i go kilim pig blong i kam wan haeman
He started with the first rank.
mwe stat lan urut mane gulgul
He started with the first rank and the second rank.
i stat long urut wetem gulgul [narapela step]
The first rank and the second rank.
monok, ka te nok okiye, me melah teteh okiye me van lan lokwaru
As it was finished, he went up to the third rank.
finis, taem i finis long ples ya, i jam i go long lokwaru [namba tu step]
me van lan lokwaru te nok okiye, me van mwe step lan lokwaru mwe van lan meleun
As the third rank was finished, as he had gone up to the third rank, he went up to the forth rank.
taem i go long lokwaru finis, i go i step long lokwaru finis, i go long meleun [namba tri step]
meleun kiye mwe van lam kie me meleun monok
The forth rank, they said, the forth rank was finished.
meleun ya oli talem i meleun finis
soo ka te tavela lan meleun me van lan naim
As he got the forth rank, he went up to the fifth rank.
wan taem i girap long meleun i go long naim [namba fo step]
naim kiye pon, mwi kinte tóó kingyee ye mu usilii mee ye
Now the fifth rank, he pinched the cane and follow it.
naim ya, i pincim ol waelken ya i folem i folem i kam ya
me mela lan naim kiye lap tóó woroló mu du
He went up to the fifth rank, there were two canes.
i jam long naim ya, tu waelken i stap
sen mwe dumuo tóó, sen mwe loro ke mwe pwetpwet momele
The other top of the cane, the other leaf came put sideways like this.
wan i top long waelken, narawan i lip blong hem we i silip olsem
ka bwe van lap tua, abwe mela lan mange pon ngiye lap tua
When they will stone, he will go up the custom hierarchy, now they shoud stone.
taem i go oli stonem, bae i jam long mange nao ya, oli stonem
lam tua me mela lam tua tua tua tua van ka saka lan topsoro
They stoned jumping, they kept stoning, but he did not reach there with the stones.
oli stonem i jam, oli stonem stonem stonem gogo, oli no save stonem kasem
me melamee lantan mwe te popat ka be mee ka be e mal pon ngiye
He jumped down, he killed the pig in order to became chief now.
i jam i kam daon, i kilim pig i kam i mal ya nao
mal kiye pon dyem kie ka, mwe vehe ih se yaapuo ke to bo ke dyem kie ka
The chief, we say now, he carries the name of chief as we say.
mal ya nao yumi talem se, i karem nem ya hae man we yumi talem se
He will plant a chief palm.
bae i planem stamba blong namele
mwe bá liimwee kiye nge kom lehe liimwee soo mwe pwettone Neten kiye okorok
He planted this chief palm, now you still see a chief palm in Neten, this place far away.
i planem namele ya we yu luk wan namele i stap behaen long Neten olgeta longwe
lam kie Memeli kege kim du kim kie kastom jip Memeli
They call him Memeli, you are calling him custom chief, Memeli.
oli talem Memeli we yufala i stap talem kastom jip Memeli
Memeli kiye me yee se mal ke mwe gelé
that Memeli is the wood of the chief (...)
Memeli ya i wud blong mal we i pem
vanten ngyee lare kiibele ke mwe gelé Memeli kiye pan woró veh
The men did not know how much did Memeli pay for his mouth. (?)
ol man oli no save se i pem Memeli ya hamas maot blong hem
anap kie gon mane kip kiibele ke popat ke mwe gelé Memeli lii mwee kiye me gelé popat werivyet
I will just say, so that you know, that the pig which Memeli paid for the chief palm, he paid four. pigs.
bae mi talem nomo long yufala i save se pig we i pem Memeli stamba blong namele ya i pem fo pig
mwe gelé mu dumuo me bá liimwee me van lon tan
First one he paid, he planted the chief palm in the ground.
i pem festaem i planem namele i go long graon
ngale ka te topne loro soo, popat soo
As it got a leaf, one pig.
afta taem i sakem wan kip blong hem, wan pig
ngale ka te mee te pyong, popat soo
As it started to have blossoms, one pig.
afta taem i putum flaoa, wan pig
ka te pa were, popat soo
As it gave fruits, one pig.
taem i putum frut, wan pig
mane nap kie ke yaapuo kingyee lam mee yaapuo du okele
So, I should say, the men became high man there.
olsem bae mi talem ol man ya oli kam hae man long ples ya
mal okele saa step ngyee lam van e yaapuo okiye
The chief made the steps in order to become the high man there.
mal long ples ya ol step blong olgeta oli go oli hae man long ples ya
nap pune bomiye gon kap kiibele
I'll tell it this way, so that you know.
mi talem olsem ya bae yufala i save
bili ke mwi syivye popat kiye werivyet ye, popat kingyee ye mon mak en mu du
As he killed the four pigs, the mark stayed.
taem i kilim fo pig ya, ol pig ya mak blong olgeta i stap
kiyem syivye popat ke mwe ling soo
They killed the pig, it was the first step.
oli kilim pig we i wan step
ke mwe bá liimwee me van lon tan, popat kege mwi tili wilin bogon gon
As he planted the chief palm in the ground, the pig whose tusks just poked the mouth (i.e. formed a single circle).
taem i planem namele i go long graon, pig ya [tut blong pig] i stikim skin blong maot nomo
bili ke lo mwee soo te toaa te soaa, dumuo lo mwee soo te mwe soaa
As the lief of the chief palm came out, came out, the first leaf of the chief palm came out.
taem we wan lif blong namele i kamaot, wan top blong namele i kamaot
mwi syivye popat ke luwen mwe soaa
He killed the pig which got a tooth.
i kilim pig we tut blong hem i kamaot
ngale ka lii mwee te pyong,
Then the chief palm started to have flowers.
afta taem namele i putum flaoa
mwe syivye popat ke luwen mwe stat mwe mwebing
He killed the pig whose teeth started to bend.
i kilim pig we tut blong hem i stat tanem
me van ka te lingi were, mwe syivye popat ke luwen mo kopih
As it gave fruits, he killed the pig whose teeth were round.
i go taem i putum frut, i kilim pig we tut blong hem i kam raon
me mee mwe tili bwiri bot lép
He came and poked the stems of the teeth. (? tili -- break)
i kam i stikim stamba blong tut
mal ngiye, mo gone san moko pon ngiye
The chief, he made his reputation now.
bigman ya nao, i mekem nius blong hem i go nao
anap pune gon ngiye, notnoten mee ke dyeme lan step van me e mal
I'll just tell, the thought that we make a step to became chief.
mi talem olsem nomo, tingting we yumi kam long step we i go i hae man
i stap long ples ya i kam
He started with the first rank.
Then he went up to the third rank.
te van lan lokwaru monok, me van e naim
Then he went up to the third rank and then he went up to the fifth rank.
i go long lokwaru finis, i go i naim
ka te naim tenok, me van lan step ka be van be mal pon ngiye
As he finished the fifth rank, he went up, he became the chief.
taem i naim finis, i go long step we bae i go i hae man nao
naim kiye nge nge, kom longane lam kie olfela kiyee le sayee taata Mansop naim
Now this is the fifth rank, you hear, they say, the old man there, their father Mansop (has) the fifth rank.
naim ya, yu harem oli talem ol olfela ya papa blong olgeta Mansop naim
kiyem vehe van pán joj okorok nam idi san tóó van nam kinte nam kie okorok
They bring (him) to the church place far away, I took his cane, pinched it and said over there.
oli karem i go long jioj lowe mi karem wael ken mi pinsim mi talem longwe
kop lehe tóó soo mo pwet, a dumuoro mwe pwet a loro soo momele mining ke
You see, there is one cane and first it stayed and there was one leaf like this. (film!)
yu luk wan waelken i stap, be top blong hem i stap be wan lip blong hem i olsem i mining
me e naim ngiye, me van ka alap tua ngiye
It is the fith rank now, they will stone now.
i naim ya, i go blong oli stonem nao
lap tua, pon ka te kinkuoro dumuo tóó, a bwe kinkuoro loro ke mwe saa pwet ye, abwe e mal
They will stone now, the first who brake the cane and break its leaf, he will be the chief.
oli stonem, spos i pincimbrekem top blong waelken, mo i pincimbrekem lip we i hang i stap ya, bae i hae man
peete, a skul me mee ngale me mee lon skul
It is near, he came to the church, then he came to the church.
klosap, skul i kam, afta i kam long skul
